+
+      // [netplay] Wire session creation to the broker. The HOST flag tells us
+      // whether this instance is hosting or (post-search) joining. We fill the
+      // guest XSESSION_INFO so the title's connect path has a real peer XNADDR.
+      //
+      // CRITICAL: the XDK XSESSION_INFO layout is
+      //   { XNKID sessionID[8]; XNADDR hostAddress[36]; XNKEY keyExchangeKey[16]; }
+      // i.e. the 8-byte session id comes FIRST (offset 0), the 36-byte XNADDR at
+      // +8, the 16-byte key at +44. The title reads sessionID.ab[0] to recognise
+      // an online session (must be 0xAE per XNKID_ONLINE); if that byte is wrong
